<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Darianne on 03-22-2001 07:51 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">
Re travel spells: 

Sure, Sow and Ports get you there "quickly" but other spells help you get there safly, and possibly quicker.

By this I mean Levitate (Mmm... 10k drops in some areas), Invis (useful in tons of places), and Enduring Breath (limited usefulness, but would still be an asset if we got it).  Yes, there are potions available, its just a pain keeping them all, and its possible you may run out in a given night.

The only levitate item in the game is all but impossible to get.  There are now two EB items that I know about off the top of my head... one being the fishbone earring... an easy (but always camped) camp.. or buy from 2-5k depending on your seller.  The shield from the turtle being the other.  No invis items (that clerics can use, woot warriors) exist that I know about.

On mana regen:

Wizards get thier harvest spell.  Wizards (and I think Necros, but I'm really not sure) get that "shieldskin" upgrade post 50 which add 1 mana/tick.  Harvest is the real nice one... but hey, 1mana/tick is better than 0 extra per tick.

Mages get Mod Rods.  Definatly not something you just summon when you need mana, cause they cost a lot... but its possible to have on on you for later, and have them on friends.  More useful to give back other peoples mana in raid times (ie: Mage, summon rods and drop them)

Enchanters get thier clarity lines, they also have thier insight/brilliance lines, and the new +mana lines (Gift).

Necros are kings and queens of getting mana.

Druids get some post 50 spell... mask of the hunter or something?  Like the wizard shield spell, it adds 1mana/tick regen.  Now druids get a spell at 60, which is less hp than what our buffs do... but offers "Breeze" level mana regen that aparently stacks with other forms of mana regen.  Who'd want the cleric hp/ac line again?

Shamans have thier very nice Cannie line, I play a shaman and the line is amazing.

---------

Am I a bit jealous of this stuff?  Of course... I'd love to have some mana regen... either as a constant effect (clarity like) or a direct surge (harvest, cannie).   I know clerics have advantages now..... having reach post 49, death is trivial unless I expertly lose my body somewhere.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
</table>

